1
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:22,290
(Meiwan Town, 1991)

2
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:35,600
(Grandma,)

3
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,039
(I'm going to join you.)

4
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,799
(I really can't hold on any longer.)

5
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,920
(I've tried so hard,)

6
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,520
(exhausting every possible method.)

7
00:00:45,039 --> 00:00:47,280
(But I can never escape Meiwan Town)

8
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:50,079
(or get away from him.)

9
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:51,920
(I'm so tired.)

10
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:55,039
(I only have this last bit
of strength left.)

11
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:57,520
(So I chose this path.)

12
00:00:58,679 --> 00:01:00,920
(Right now, I don't even know
whom to say goodbye to.)

13
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:04,320
(Then let it be
my nineteen-year-old self.)

14
00:01:07,399 --> 00:01:09,439
(If my life could start over,)

15
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,560
(I wish
I could have a chance to choose.)

16
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,359
(To Ye Haitang, September 3, 1991)

17
00:01:13,359 --> 00:01:14,040
(Goodbye.)

18
00:01:24,089 --> 00:01:28,565
(Beixing City, 2026)

19
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,840
Who's it? What are you doing?

20
00:01:58,879 --> 00:01:59,480
Stop!

21
00:02:02,239 --> 00:02:03,560
I can see you.

22
00:02:03,959 --> 00:02:04,560
Listen up.

23
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,400
This pitchfork here won't show mercy.

24
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:51,208
=Twelve Letters=

25
00:02:51,208 --> 00:02:54,088
=Episode 1=
=The Letter Writer=

26
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:10,599
Sir,

27
00:03:11,879 --> 00:03:13,719
if you come in daily and won't leave,

28
00:03:13,719 --> 00:03:15,000
I'll lose my job.

29
00:03:15,319 --> 00:03:16,879
Have some pity on me, will you?

30
00:03:17,879 --> 00:03:19,039
Just do your work.

31
00:03:19,719 --> 00:03:20,719
What work?

32
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:23,439
My main job is keeping people
from wandering in,

33
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,560
specifically keeping you out.

34
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,759
I need to get you out.

35
00:03:27,599 --> 00:03:28,800
I'm just a security guard.

36
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,199
This job wasn't easy to get.

37
00:03:30,599 --> 00:03:31,400
Go to my supervisor

38
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,479
if you need anything, okay?

39
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,599
Stop torturing me.

40
00:03:35,479 --> 00:03:36,360
What's today's date?

41
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,919
Dunno. I can't remember either.

42
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,439
Want some?

43
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:46,088
We've known each other

44
00:03:46,088 --> 00:03:46,879
for two months.

45
00:03:46,879 --> 00:03:48,560
That counts as some friendship, right?

46
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,919
Be honest with me.

47
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:53,719
What are you doing

48
00:03:53,719 --> 00:03:55,039
sitting here every day?

49
00:03:58,719 --> 00:03:59,599
Waiting for a letter.

50
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:01,599
A letter?

51
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,039
You mean this?

52
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:05,919
It contains no letters.

53
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:07,479
Nobody writes letters these days.

54
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:11,479
It's fake, isn't it?

55
00:04:11,639 --> 00:04:12,800
What are you saying?

56
00:04:13,479 --> 00:04:14,199
It's real!

57
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:17,120
Okay, it's real.

58
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,639
But they're closing for today.

59
00:04:18,639 --> 00:04:19,840
Come mail tomorrow, okay?

60
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:20,599
You go ahead.

61
00:04:23,319 --> 00:04:23,920
Fine.

62
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:26,199
Wait all you want then.

63
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,360
Go see a doctor.

64
00:04:28,959 --> 00:04:29,639
Such a nuisance.

65
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,800
Ma'am, can you please
keep an eye on your dad?

66
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,639
They're tearing the place down.
No trespassing.

67
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:38,639
My coworker and I
fought him this morning.

68
00:04:38,639 --> 00:04:40,519
Just watch your dad, alright?

69
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:44,319
Let's go home.

70
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,720
I'm not going.

71
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:47,439
Let's go home, Dad. It's freezing.

72
00:04:47,439 --> 00:04:48,600
It's not time yet.

73
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,560
What 'time'?

74
00:04:49,759 --> 00:04:51,040
Come home with me.

75
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:52,240
Why?

76
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:54,079
Why did you come back here again?

77
00:04:54,079 --> 00:04:56,560
You won't stop
until they call the police, will you?

78
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:03,920
Sir,

79
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,680
you're back.

80
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,360
I'm not moving.

81
00:05:06,279 --> 00:05:06,600
Dad.

82
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,240
Sir, we agreed...

83
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,279
Let's talk.

84
00:05:11,439 --> 00:05:12,439
I'm really sorry.

85
00:05:12,439 --> 00:05:14,199
My dad just came from the hospital.

86
00:05:14,199 --> 00:05:15,560
His heart's acting up bad.

87
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:17,000
The doctor said it's serious.

88
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,600
Why's he
always 'back from the hospital'?

89
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,120
Yes.

90
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,680
Can you move out in the next few days?

91
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:22,319
My boss said...

92
00:05:22,319 --> 00:05:23,360
We'll definitely move.

93
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,199
I bought the tickets already.
We'll move.

94
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,600
About the terms we agreed on,

95
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,920
I've sorted them out. Look.

96
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,560
Thank you.

97
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,199
Then sign here.

98
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:30,888
- Okay.
- The pen.

99
00:05:31,199 --> 00:05:32,000
How about this?

100
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,360
Let me check with my dad first.

101
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,560
Then I'll sign it immediately

102
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,560
and bring it to you.

103
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,439
I know it's been hard for you guys,

104
00:05:37,439 --> 00:05:38,360
coming over here.

105
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:40,000
It's freezing cold today.

106
00:05:40,199 --> 00:05:41,680
You guys head back to rest first.

107
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:42,560
Make it quick.

108
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,600
- Sure.
- This is urgent.

109
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,480
My dad needs his meds.

110
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,120
It's his heart.

111
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,360
Just wait.

112
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:47,600
Update me soon.

113
00:05:47,759 --> 00:05:48,439
Absolutely.

114
00:05:48,439 --> 00:05:49,439
Thanks. I appreciate it.

115
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:50,560
Here.

116
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,800
I need your ID card for the tickets.

117
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,439
Your ID card.

118
00:06:01,199 --> 00:06:01,920
Fine.

119
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,120
Miaomiao,

120
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,920
can you get me a car?

121
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:15,399
My dad and I are going

122
00:06:15,399 --> 00:06:16,120
to Beijing.

123
00:06:16,639 --> 00:06:17,480
No need to be big.

124
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,319
Tomorrow or the day after.

125
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,199
Make it fast.

126
00:06:21,879 --> 00:06:22,360
Thank you.

127
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:23,240
I'm not leaving.

128
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,560
Either

129
00:06:28,879 --> 00:06:29,800
we go to Beijing,

130
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:30,680
or

131
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,480
we'll both stay in this dump

132
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,639
and rot here forever.

133
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,040
I need to call Mingxiao

134
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,240
to have him talk to you.

135
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,560
Why call him?

136
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,879
I broke up with him ages ago.

137
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:43,560
Why?

138
00:06:43,759 --> 00:06:44,439
Why?

139
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:46,839
Because he thought I was a burden.

140
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,560
You won't go to Beijing.

141
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:49,920
If anything happens here,

142
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,120
I have to rush back.

143
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,680
If you keep making a fuss,

144
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,560
I'll even lose my job in Beijing.

145
00:06:57,439 --> 00:06:58,439
I'll take my meds.

146
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,279
Wait.

147
00:07:00,439 --> 00:07:02,120
Why are you taking meds now?

148
00:07:02,439 --> 00:07:03,600
You refuse to see a doctor.

149
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,120
What good are these meds alone?

150
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,120
Yu Zhiyong,

151
00:07:06,319 --> 00:07:07,680
let's settle this today.

152
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,160
You keep saying
you're waiting for letters.

153
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,680
Who's actually writing to you?

154
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,800
Not waiting.

155
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,360
I'm sending letters.

156
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,800
I'm sending letters.

157
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,800
I'm done with your nonsense.

158
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,240
Tomorrow,

159
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,360
we're leaving.

160
00:07:23,759 --> 00:07:24,600
No delay.

161
00:07:25,319 --> 00:07:26,000
Nian,

162
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:26,920
I take the meds.

163
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:27,560
Go away.

164
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,360
The meds.

165
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,759
The meds.

166
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,600
The meds.

167
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,240
I'm taking the meds.

168
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:25,879
Miaomiao.

169
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,639
10 AM works.

170
00:08:28,639 --> 00:08:30,079
Send me the driver's number.

171
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:32,560
Don't come.

172
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:33,959
We'll move by ourselves.

173
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,800
I'll message you when we reach Beijing.

174
00:08:44,759 --> 00:08:45,240
Dad,

175
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,440
what would you like?

176
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,200
Dad,

177
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:52,360
you...

178
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,000
Where did you go?

179
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,639
(I don't want to leave.)

180
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,799
(I don't want to burden you)

181
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,320
(or make you angry.)

182
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,840
(For me, this illness)

183
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,320
(is not all bad.)

184
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,639
(I need to do something important.)

185
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,320
(When it's done,)

186
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,200
(I'll come back on my own.)

187
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:30,960
This is my dad.

188
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,440
Officer, this is my dad.

189
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,440
See? I told you
he was still at the factory.

190
00:09:34,559 --> 00:09:35,919
Let's keep searching.

191
00:09:36,039 --> 00:09:37,799
Wait, are you sure it's him

192
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:39,039
just from that back view?

193
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:40,039
I'm sure.

194
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,440
That's what he was wearing.

195
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,320
He's been showing up
around here a lot lately.

196
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:45,039
The factory was checked.

197
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:46,000
He's not here.

198
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,600
How about this?

199
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,039
We'll head back to the station,

200
00:09:49,279 --> 00:09:51,399
review the nearby surveillance footage,

201
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:53,039
and keep searching with patrol cars.

202
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:53,840
Don't panic.

203
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:56,039
Officer, here's the thing.

204
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:57,720
My dad sometimes

205
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:58,840
gets confused.

206
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:00,200
I'm very worried about him

207
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,639
now that he's out there alone.

208
00:10:02,159 --> 00:10:03,639
You knew about your dad's condition

209
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:04,519
and you provoked him?

210
00:10:04,799 --> 00:10:06,320
Yeah, that was my fault.

211
00:10:06,559 --> 00:10:07,200
Head back first.

212
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,679
We'll call you if anything comes up.

213
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:09,559
(Security Room)
Okay.

214
00:10:09,559 --> 00:10:10,200
Bye, officers.

215
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,440
Call me immediately
if there's news, officers.

216
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:13,919
Okay.

217
00:10:13,919 --> 00:10:15,639
Thank you.

218
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,759
Ma'am? Ma'am?

219
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:24,600
Ma'am?

220
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,440
Do you need something?

221
00:10:32,679 --> 00:10:33,440
Hello.

222
00:10:34,159 --> 00:10:35,399
I'm Zhang Quan,

223
00:10:35,399 --> 00:10:36,200
a security guard.

224
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,159
Do you remember me?

225
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:39,080
You picked up your dad from me.

226
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,679
I gave him a band-aid that time.

227
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:41,919
I remember you.

228
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,000
Do you need something?

229
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,240
Your dad's missing, isn't he?

230
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:47,440
Have you seen him?

231
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:48,799
Let me be clear first.

232
00:10:49,159 --> 00:10:50,080
I'm not crazy.

233
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,200
I'm telling the truth.

234
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,440
If you believe me, I'll tell...

235
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,960
I believe you. Go ahead.

236
00:10:55,799 --> 00:10:57,200
That night,

237
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,639
I was at my post doing my job...

238
00:11:12,679 --> 00:11:14,320
Fine! You want to play it this way?

239
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:16,399
Sneaking over while I was asleep.

240
00:11:21,159 --> 00:11:22,600
Sir, you're back again.

241
00:11:23,919 --> 00:11:26,080
Why not come inside for dumplings?

242
00:11:27,559 --> 00:11:28,519
You're late today.

243
00:11:29,039 --> 00:11:30,279
What? Expecting letters again?

244
00:11:38,159 --> 00:11:39,039
I'm mailing a letter.

245
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:40,679
Mailing now, huh?

246
00:11:41,639 --> 00:11:43,200
Alright. Leave after mailing it, okay?

247
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,039
Go home, okay?

248
00:11:48,639 --> 00:11:49,200
Just go.

249
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:54,440
Sir?

250
00:12:00,919 --> 00:12:02,639
What now?

251
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,679
Playing hide-and-seek?

252
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,399
I see you there.

253
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:12,559
Sir?

254
00:12:15,559 --> 00:12:16,559
This is getting creepy.

255
00:12:29,279 --> 00:12:31,039
What? Did he crawl into the mailbox?

256
00:12:42,159 --> 00:12:43,440
So you're saying

257
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,480
the letter just disappeared?

258
00:12:45,679 --> 00:12:46,559
The letter's gone.

259
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,039
And so is he.

260
00:12:51,399 --> 00:12:53,200
Stop talking nonsense, will you?

261
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,320
If you did see my dad,

262
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:56,080
try to remember which direction he went.

263
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,159
So I can tell the police
for them to search properly.

264
00:12:58,799 --> 00:13:00,279
Why are you like this?

265
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,679
Didn't I just tell you?

266
00:13:01,679 --> 00:13:02,200
You said

267
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,496
you believed me, so I told you.

268
00:13:03,639 --> 00:13:04,919
What would I gain from lying?

269
00:13:06,559 --> 00:13:08,080
Ma'am, let's stop talking here.

270
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:09,720
This place feels creepy. Let's go.

271
00:13:09,919 --> 00:13:10,799
You go.

272
00:13:11,559 --> 00:13:12,600
You won't leave? Fine.

273
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,679
Stay here by yourself then.

274
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,799
You are both nuts.

275
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,519
The letter's really gone?

276
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,440
Dad,

277
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,440
please come home.

278
00:13:26,679 --> 00:13:28,159
I was wrong before.

279
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,279
I shouldn't have pushed.

280
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,159
Come back.

281
00:13:31,679 --> 00:13:32,600
We won't move.

282
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,200
Whatever issues we have,

283
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,679
let's discuss them properly.

284
00:13:51,799 --> 00:13:52,559
Was that the cat?

285
00:13:53,159 --> 00:13:54,120
Ma'am, don't be scared.

286
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,080
The cat meowed, right?

287
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,279
The same cat you mentioned?

288
00:13:56,799 --> 00:13:57,279
Yes.

289
00:13:57,679 --> 00:13:58,440
Don't be afraid.

290
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,000
